137.title: Afterparty & Networking
137.description: Afterparty is a great time to have some fun and meet new people

136.title: GDG Los Angeles DevFest 2016 Opening

109.title: U & I
109.description: Romain and Chet share information and techniques for making better animations and using color correctly in Android UIs.

108.title: Innovative rapid prototyping: The Creative Technologist's ToolKit
108.description: As a Creative Technologist, it is his job to know something about everything that matters. Strap yourself in for a fast paced overview of some of the top technologies Jason has been using / discovered over the past year, their creative uses, and some inspiring demos from machine learning to web services and more.

107.title: The Next Gen Web
107.description: After a brief intro to give some context on why mobile web is important, I will cover AMP, and PWA; new technologies to enable app-like experiences and reliable performance on the mobile web. Finally I will cover a less sexy, but relevant topic https. Finally, and totally disconnected from the main topic, I will talk a little bit about our Launchpad program.

106.title: 10 Awesome Features of Progressive Web Apps
106.description: Progressive Web Apps are a super exciting way to take advantage of web's power, but as a new thing they can be confusing. This talk walks you through 10 aspects that make up Progressive Web Apps and how awesome they are.

105.title: RxJava for Android
105.description: RxJava is getting popular. I'd like to share why I started with RxJava, the benefits and caveats comes with it, some tips for Android, and look head to RxJava 2.

104.title: Kotlin & Java for fun and profit
104.description: Adding Kotlin isn't really that hard. We'll go over the basics of Kotlin, how it can help you, and how you can get started with it in your existing app.

103.title: Firebase & Polymer
103.description: Leading Firebase expert, Justin Ribeiro makes using the latest Firebase features look easy.

102.title: Google Maps APIs latest information
102.description: World renown expert Masashi Katsumata will provide a deep dive into the latest Google Maps APIs and how to use them in native and hybrid apps.

101.title: Build It or Buy It
101.description: There's a constant tension between developers and developer tools providers. Developers want to use services and infrastructure, and service providers want to lock you into their platforms. Lock-in isn't always a bad thing, as long as you continue to get the service. But sometimes, like the Facebook Parse shutdown earlier this year, services go away. My talk will explore that tension, what motivates developer tools companies, and what motivates developers. And I'll discuss strategies to evaluate new developer tools, and mitigate the impact of lock-in.
